
1. Copy the files to your own directory.

2. Modify inet.h to reflect the host you are currently logged into.
   Also, modify the port numbers to be used to reduce the likelihood
   of conflicting with another server.

3. Compile the source code using the command: make

4. Start the directory server with ./directoryServer2

5. Start up the servers with ./chatServer2 <topicName> <portNumber>  --port number must be between 40000 and 65535 non-inclusive

6. start up a client with ./chatClient2 
- select the chatServer you want to connect to by selecting the number corresponding with the chat server
- enter in a username
- send messages

7. Remember to kill the server before logging off




